Our lieutenant never drank coffee in Vietnam, he still doesn’t drink it today. But often in the field or back in the rear, he would stir up a cup of chocolate, and come on over to our positions and for no particular reason, he would just sit there and began to talk. <br><br>
He was from Malibu California and on the back of his flak jacket, a Marine had taken a Magic Marker©  and written, Malibu Dreamer. Out in the field, we knew him mostly from his back, because we saw it so often, because it was he that led us into battle and we respected him greatly for that. <br><br>
When he came over to our fox holes, we didn’t expect him to have a reason for coming over,  we were just glad that he dropped by for a chat.<br><br>
This thread is just like that, a place for Foxhole chats. A point where anyone can just drop by and chat anytime for any reason on any topic. Just bring your own tin cup, I’ll keep the water boiling for coffee or hot chocolate. <br>

